---
import Lesson from "../layouts/Lesson.astro";
---

<Lesson
  title="Devices"
  lessonId="1"
  description="All devices are different, but some functions are seen across all platforms. Let's explore them."
>
  <img
    slot="hero"
    src="/assets/devices/devices.svg"
    alt="Devices Hero Image"
    class="md:max-w-[35rem] md:max-h-[35rem] w-5/6 h-auto"
  />

  <section
    class="grid grid-flow-row grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 m-4 max-w-[90vw] mx-auto"
  >
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl text-slate-800 font-semibold">Taskbars</h1>
      <p class="pt-2 text-xl text-slate-600 mb-3.5">
        Almost all devices have a top and/or bottom taskbar, these allow you to
        access things you need often quickly and easily.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src="assets/devices/MacOS_desktop.jpg"
        alt="MacOS desktop"
        class="m-auto mb-4 md:max-w-md w-5/6 h-auto"
      />
      <p class="text-base text-slate-600 text-center">
        MacOS - <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold">Top</span> and
        <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold">Bottom</span> Taskbars
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src="assets/devices/windows_desktop.png"
        alt="Windows desktop"
        class="m-auto mb-4 md:max-w-md w-5/6 h-auto"
      />
      <p class="text-base text-slate-600 text-center">
        Windows - <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold">Bottom</span>
        Taskbar
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-slate-800 font-semibold">Start Buttons</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 md:w-[40ch] pt-2">
        A start button can be used to search a device for programs or files, its
        look and location differ depending on device.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src="assets/devices/apple_logo.png"
        alt="Apple logo"
        class="max-w-[10rem] h-auto mb-4"
      />
      <p class="text-base text-slate-600 text-center">
        Located - <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold">Top Left</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src="assets/devices/windows_logo.png"
        alt=""
        class="max-w-[10rem] h-auto mb-4"
      />
      <p class="text-base text-slate-600 text-center">
        Located - <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold">Bottom Left</span> or
        <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold"> Center</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="md:mr-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-slate-800 font-semibold">File Explorers</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 md:w-[40ch] pt-2">
        The file explorer is comprised of folders and files. Folders can hold
        your files to keep them organized. There are some default folders such
        as divs, documents, and downloads as well as folders you can make
        yourself.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src="assets/devices/Finder.png"
        alt="MacOS Finder"
        class="m-auto mb-4 md:max-w-md w-5/6 h-auto"
      />
      <p class="text-base text-slate-600 text-center">
        MacOS - <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold">Finder</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center">
      <img
        src="assets/devices/File_Explorer.png"
        alt="Windows desktop"
        class="m-auto mb-4 border md:max-w-md w-5/6 h-auto"
      />
      <p class="text-base text-slate-600 text-center">
        Windows - <span class="text-[#ec598b] font-semibold"
          >Windows File Explorer</span
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Lesson>
